blematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that la=
y buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one.=
 If one overcomes the notion "I am the body", there may be another notion i=
n one's body-mind complex that one's awareness clings on to (e.g. a great d=
octor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme e=
xample, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescu=
es the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescu=
