>>>Dear all, Just wanted to warn people of kundalini s=
yndrome based on my recent experience of a patient of mine. I am doing a ps=
ychiatry job at present, and have been involved in the care of someone who =
seems to think she has had a spontaneous awakening of their kundalini since=
 childhood. This has involved out-of-body experiences and surges of energy =
in the body. She is not of Indian origin and had never heard of kundalini u=
ntil her symptoms started and she searched for an explanation. We have not =
been able to find anything physically wrong with her (all tests normal)- so=
 it might be that this is due to deranged kundalini. Many people we call me=
ntally ill describe themselves as having a spiritual crisis, or unwanted sp=
ontaneous kundalini awakening- this has triggered interest and research int=
o this topic in mainstream psychiatry. Unfortunately these patients are not=
 well-understood by western medicine, and as we have no treatments for dera=
nged
 kundalini, we struggle to help them. Many yogis try to forcibly waken=
 the kundalini. My experience with this lady confirmed my feeling that kund=
alini should not be forcibly wakened. This woman wants to kill herself at t=
imes because the suffering from the deranged energy is so bad. She feels it=
 will consume her, and it is something she cannot escape from. I wondered w=
hat solution there could be to her problem. The logical one was to pray to =
the Divine Mother, who manifests as the kundalini to relieve the suffering =
of this woman- and either cure her, or give her the strength to bear this. =
May I request that the good samaritans among you pray for her, and for othe=
rs like her (whom we may not know of)- their suffering really is pitiable. =
And let us be careful in our sadhana so as not to end up in this situation =
ourselves. Perhaps this is why the bhakti marga is the safest. It is perhap=
s safest to say "let me be your instrument" and leave the kundalini
 rising=
 bit to God's will. Om Dum Durgayai Namaha Aparna 
